N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 22 ยง 121.1 - General

State Regulations

All temporary assignments of judges to the

Supreme Court from a court of limited jurisdiction, other than the Court of

Claims, or designations of eligibility for such assignments, shall be made by
the Chief Administrator of the Courts, in his or her discretion, upon
consultation with and agreement of the presiding justice of the appropriate

Appellate Division, pursuant to Part 33 of the Rules of the Chief Judge and in
accordance with the procedure set forth in this Part. Notes
